ğŸ” Why?
Because in C++, when you pass an array to a function, the array decays into a pointer to its first element. So:

cpp
Copy
Edit
void func(int arr[])
and

cpp
Copy
Edit
void func(int *arr)
are functionally identical. Both are treated by the compiler as:

cpp
Copy
Edit
void func(int *arr)
Thatâ€™s why you'll often see people just write int* arr â€” it's more honest about whatâ€™s happening under the hood.

